The paper discusses graph-based semi-supervised learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of non-linear methods such as node embeddings and graph convolutional networks (GCN) is also mentioned, which are popular topics in the subfields of deep learning and artificial intelligence. The paper's focus on improving the performance of SSL methods suggests that it may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the use of graph structures and diffusion processes may also place it under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
